00062| def solve2(G: Graph, final_objs, initial_objs=None, contains=True):
00063|     """
00064|     Solve constraints to determine if vulnerable paths are feasible and generate exploits.
00065| 
00066|     This function builds a Z3 constraint system from the CONTRIBUTES_TO edges in the
00067|     graph, modeling how values flow through operations like string concatenation and
00068|     numeric addition. It then solves the constraints to:
00069|     1. Determine if a vulnerable path is actually reachable (feasibility)
00070|     2. Generate concrete input values that would trigger the vulnerability (exploit)
00071| 
00072|     The constraint system is built by:
00073|     - Following CONTRIBUTES_TO edges backward from sink objects
00074|     - Modeling operations (string_concat, numeric_add) as Z3 constraints
00075|     - Adding constraints for literal values found in the graph
00076|     - Applying extra constraints from G.extra_constraints
00077| 
00078|     Args:
00079|         G (Graph): The graph object containing the analysis results
00080|         final_objs (list): List of sink object node IDs to solve for. These are
00081|             the objects that reach vulnerable functions.
00082|         initial_objs (list, optional): List of source object node IDs. If provided,
00083|             only solutions for these objects are returned. Defaults to None.
