00087|     Yields:
00088|         tuple: (assertions, results) where:
00089|             - assertions: Z3 assertions (constraints) that were added to the solver
00090|             - results: Either "failed" if unsat, or a dict mapping variable names to
00091|               their concrete values (the exploit payload)
00092| 
00093|     Example:
00094|         >>> # Solve for OS command injection exploit
00095|         >>> G.solve_from = "; rm -rf /"  # Desired payload in sink
00096|         >>> for assertions, results in solve2(G, [sink_obj], [source_obj]):
00097|         ...     if results != "failed":
00098|         ...         print("Exploit found:", results)
00099|         ...         # results contains input values that produce the payload
00100|     """
00101|     time1 = time.time()
00102|     print(
00103|         "final objs:", final_objs, "value:", G.solve_from, "initial objs:", initial_objs
