_Thinking:_

We've improved the coverage from 13% to... wait, it's still 13%. The issue is that the main modules (opgen.py, graph.py, launcher.py) are the biggest and they have very low coverage. These need the integration tests.

Let me look at the coverage for `jsflow/utils/helpers.py` - we improved it from 45% to 53%.

The challenge is that most of the codebase is in opgen.py, graph.py, and launcher.py, which require complex integration tests that depend on npm/esprima.

To reach 60% coverage, I would need to either:
